{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/head-injury/background-information/incidence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"aaf5f98d-0894-5834-80e7-77201ed31f90","slug":"incidence","fullItemName":"Incidence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 81702ab5-8270-45d9-bfd8-a06b6d6ba477 --><h2>Incidence</h2><!-- end field 81702ab5-8270-45d9-bfd8-a06b6d6ba477 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item ac094cd5-c959-444b-b5c2-5adbcb01c956 --><!-- begin field 217220d8-44eb-4015-87a4-df5383d86574 --><p><strong>The incidence of head injury is difficult to assess as it varies according to the study definitions used and the point in the care pathway when people with head injury are assessed.</strong></p><ul><li>Each year, 1.4 million people attend emergency departments in England and Wales with a recent head injury, and 33–50% of these are children aged under 15 years [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">NICE, 2014c</a>].<ul><li>A UK prospective survey of case notes of children aged less than 15 years who were admitted to hospital (n = 5700) found that the peak prevalence of hospital admission for head injury was in infants (19.2% of admissions) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">Trefan et al, 2015</a>].</li></ul></li><li>The annual incidence at UK emergency departments of people with a head injury is about 6.6% [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">SIGN, 2009</a>].</li><li>About 90% of people attending emergency departments with a head injury have a minor head injury [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">Trefan et al, 2015</a>].</li><li>About 200,000 people are admitted to hospital each year with a head injury [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">NICE, 2014c</a>]. This equates to about 20% of all people attending an emergency department with a head injury being admitted to hospital [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/head-injury/references/\">SIGN, 2009</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 217220d8-44eb-4015-87a4-df5383d86574 --><!-- end item ac094cd5-c959-444b-b5c2-5adbcb01c956 -->","topic":{"id":"9c82c71c-776b-5830-a9b5-f2a1f6e35152","topicId":"22e7906b-f704-4d08-a97c-ab54e669323e","topicName":"Head injury","slug":"head-injury","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2016","chapters":[{"id":"36484ef0-87eb-5854-8fc9-13ff9e51cd78","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a7070078-af1b-59a5-a752-8e5e04278465","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"8fdc6898-f17a-5206-ae63-22888799fa23","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"dd05f53c-9e78-5093-955c-34fc3983198b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"18750411-4e80-5f36-987b-228e2d67354c","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"9af40024-874c-5272-93d0-6d40a04c0a49","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"ce894088-4f08-53d3-b4e0-ce8a765c1dd4","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8dcefa1c-0e26-5c37-ba8b-0e73706e501e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"840e3ede-e526-5282-a63f-af07547e24e4","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"7cab23d8-916a-5694-9eef-78887f368d1f","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"6a9d6f45-556a-5ade-9ff6-d32d2f7a5bb7","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"04a64b49-1bfc-5ccc-b972-367a10a3d60c","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"f3